:: Copper Word Accepted [venue-cellar] {"position":"2100,500","size":"100,100"}
(set: $awaitingCopperPwd to false)\
<div class="cellar-scene">
<div class="cellar-light"></div>
You say the words you were given. Copper's eyebrows freeze as they are rising, and in the throttling of momentum seem to rise above themselves, like ghosts, in placid supplication. Then his masseters, their wreck-head sneer, become again the tyrants in his visage.

'I see. We'll have it soft then. But you still knocked on my door, lad.'

He's closer. Quiet Frankie won't look up but Ashton Granger has; she stops doodling.

[[Brace yourself|Fight starts]]
</div>

:: Copper confronts [venue-cellar] {"position":"1800,700","size":"100,100"}
(set: $awaitingCopperPwd to false)\
<!-- Swinging bulb -->
<div class="cellar-bulb-wrap">
<svg width="48" height="90" viewBox="0 0 48 90"><!-- Wire from ceiling --><line x1="24" y1="0" x2="24" y2="30" stroke="#888878" stroke-width="1.4" opacity="0.75"/><!-- Socket cap --><rect x="17" y="28" width="14" height="10" rx="2.5"fill="rgba(80,78,65,0.9)" stroke="rgba(160,155,120,0.7)" stroke-width="1"/><!-- Socket ring detail --><rect x="19" y="36" width="10" height="3" rx="1"fill="none" stroke="rgba(150,145,110,0.55)" stroke-width="0.8"/><!-- Outer glow halo --><ellipse cx="24" cy="60" rx="20" ry="22"fill="rgba(255,245,160,0.12)"/><!-- Bulb body — pear shape, bright and solid --><path d="M24,38 C16,38 10,45 10,55 C10,67 16,78 24,78 C32,78 38,67 38,55 C38,45 32,38 24,38 Z"fill="rgba(255,252,210,0.95)" stroke="rgba(220,210,160,0.6)" stroke-width="0.8"/><!-- Inner warm core --><ellipse cx="24" cy="57" rx="9" ry="11"fill="rgba(255,240,120,0.55)"/><!-- Filament — W-shape --><path d="M18,60 L20,53 L24,58 L28,53 L30,60"fill="none" stroke="rgba(255,200,40,0.95)" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linejoin="round"/><!-- Neck base ring --><rect x="20" y="75" width="8" height="3" rx="1"fill="rgba(200,195,155,0.65)" stroke="none"/></svg>
</div>
<div class="cellar-scene">
<div class="cellar-light"></div>
Copper gets closer.

'I asked you a question,' he says.

[[Brace yourself|Fight starts]]
[[Stand your ground|Stand your ground]]
</div>

:: Alba Complete [piano-bed] {"position":"1550,50","size":"100,100"}
<script>(function(){/* HTTP-prefetch the iframe HTML and the THREE.js CDN script. Avoiding a hidden iframe here because Chrome throttles script execution in off-screen iframes — Three.js inits but the scene-build script never runs, and we land on Dawn Approach with an empty canvas. Plain fetch puts the HTML in the cache; the THREE library link-preload primes the network so the fresh iframe on Dawn Approach mounts fast. */try{fetch('oxford-street-from-centre-point-3d-static.html',{cache:'force-cache'});}catch(e){}if(!document.getElementById('dss-three-prefetch')){var l=document.createElement('link');l.id='dss-three-prefetch';l.rel='preload';l.as='script';l.href='https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/three.js/r128/three.min.js';document.head.appendChild(l);}})();</script>\
<div class="ending-pane">London is all before you: Tyburn, Bloomsbury, Fitzrovia; St. Giles, at your feet; and Soho, which has dulled your soul and dressed you for the sun, in midnight's cloak, throbs low and still, through its bruised capillaries.

You found the poem, the path to dawn's bleak Albion.

[[Traveller, wake!|Dawn Approach White]]</div>

:: The Fetch {"position":"1600,50","size":"100,100"}
<script>setTimeout(function(){ if (window.dssAudio) window.dssAudio.uncannyBreath(); }, 400);</script>\
<script>(function(){/* Earliest practical prefetch of the Oxford-Street iframe HTML + the Three.js CDN script. Fires here (The Fetch → Approach Centre Point → Alba Complete/Incomplete → Dawn Approach), so HTTP cache has the assets long before the iframe mounts. The later prefetch passages keep the same calls for safety; all are idempotent (HTTP cache dedup + id check on the link element). Hidden-iframe preload was ruled out previously because Chrome throttles scripts in non-visible frames. */try{fetch('oxford-street-from-centre-point-3d-static.html',{cache:'force-cache'});}catch(e){}if(!document.getElementById('dss-three-prefetch')){var l=document.createElement('link');l.id='dss-three-prefetch';l.rel='preload';l.as='script';l.href='https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/three.js/r128/three.min.js';document.head.appendChild(l);}})();</script>\
<div class="glass-pane">You see yourself walking to meet you, who looks at you, with a pitying grin, then turns and heads, quickly, towards Centre Point.

(if: $haunts's length >= 11 and not ($haunts contains $haunt12))[
(set: $haunts to $haunts + (a: $haunt12))
<div class="haunt-box">
<div class="haunt-header">⟡ HAUNT COLLECTED ⟡</div>
<div class="haunt-name">THE CROWN</div>
<div class="haunt-description">From Kether to Malkuth and back again.</div>
<div class="haunt-work"><em>The work: Exaltatio.</em></div>
<div class="haunt-progress">(print: $haunts's length) of 12 caught</div>
</div>

]\
[[Follow him|Approach Centre Point]]
(if: $lilyCount < 5 or $haunts's length < 12)[
You can leave now, perhaps it's wise to get out. But there are still flowers to gather in the night, and work yet to be done.

<span class="back-to-night-glow">[[Not yet. Back to the night.|Dean Street]]</span>]</div>

:: Alba Incomplete [piano-bed] {"position":"1550,100","size":"100,100"}
<script>(function(){/* HTTP-prefetch the iframe HTML and the THREE.js CDN script. Avoiding a hidden iframe here because Chrome throttles script execution in off-screen iframes — Three.js inits but the scene-build script never runs, and we land on Dawn Approach with an empty canvas. Plain fetch puts the HTML in the cache; the THREE library link-preload primes the network so the fresh iframe on Dawn Approach mounts fast. */try{fetch('oxford-street-from-centre-point-3d-static.html',{cache:'force-cache'});}catch(e){}if(!document.getElementById('dss-three-prefetch')){var l=document.createElement('link');l.id='dss-three-prefetch';l.rel='preload';l.as='script';l.href='https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/three.js/r128/three.min.js';document.head.appendChild(l);}})();</script>\
<div class="ending-pane ending-pane-dim">London is all before you: Tyburn, Bloomsbury, Fitzrovia; St. Giles, at your feet; and Soho, which has dulled your soul and dressed you for the sun, in midnight's cloak, throbs low and still, through its bruised capillaries.

You did not find the poem. Sometimes the night is its own work, and the dawn will come regardless.

[[Traveller, sleep!|Dawn Approach Black]]</div>

:: Dawn [dawn-end piano-bed] {"position":"1700,100","size":"100,100"}
(set: _albaComplete to ($alba contains $alba1) and ($alba contains $alba2) and ($alba contains $alba3))\
<script>
/* Ripley's Wheel always reveals on Dawn now — the wheel itself reads the
   collected $haunts from Harlowe state and only renders the alchemical /
   haunt writing for stages whose haunt the player actually caught, so the
   wheel becomes a personalised record of the night rather than an all-or-
   nothing reward. Outer setTimeout(0) defers the _passageGen snapshot
   until after the MutationObserver has incremented it for THIS passage;
   without that, the synchronous script captures the stale value and the
   cancel-guard always trips. Same race fix as showDrinkPopupSafe. */
(function(){
  setTimeout(function(){
    var pgGen = window._passageGen;
    setTimeout(function(){
      if (window._passageGen !== pgGen) return;
      if (window.dssOpusReveal) window.dssOpusReveal();
    }, 120);
  }, 0);
})();
</script>
