Copper stumbles. This will go no further; though Quiet Frankie has begun to feel for his knife.

(if: $knowsCopperWord)['I'm glad he turned you my way, son,' says Copper, now perfectly composed.
(set: $confidence to ($statGain: $confidence, 12))
[[Escape up the stairs|Standing]]]
(else:)[Copper falls about laughing. 'Good work, son! I'm sorry you picked the wrong door but that was very enjoyable stuff. Now sod off before I change my mind, but don't worry; you know me and I always remember a face.'

(set: $confidence to ($statGain: $confidence, 8))

[[Escape up the stairs|Standing]]]

