Copper looks down at his gloves as if they wrapped someone else's hands.

Quiet Frankie's smiling.

(if: $knowsCopperWord)['Not bad at all,' says Copper. 'Tell whoever sent you that they did a fine job. Very funny.'

(set: $confidence to ($statGain: $confidence, 16))
(set: $sobriety to ($statGain: $sobriety, 8))
[[Escape up the stairs|Standing]]]
(else:)[Copper wipes his lip, considers, then breaks into a grin so wide it changes the room. 'Christ. I've not seen feet like that since the war. You're wasted on whoever sent you, son. You sure you've not been at this professionally?' He claps you on the shoulder, hard enough to remind you who he is. 'Now get out of my cellar before I lose more face. And come back if you ever fancy another go.'

(set: $confidence to ($statGain: $confidence, 14))
(set: $sobriety to ($statGain: $sobriety, 6))

[[Escape up the stairs|Standing]]]

