2" cy="44" r="0.7"/><circle cx="140" cy="32" r="0.5"/><circle cx="175" cy="48" r="0.6"/><circle cx="248" cy="26" r="0.8"/><circle cx="295" cy="41" r="0.5"/><circle cx="368" cy="30" r="0.7"/><circle cx="432" cy="45" r="0.5"/></g><rect width="500" height="110" fill="url(#gs2FH)"/><rect width="500" height="110" fill="url(#gs2FV)"/></svg>

Just off the beach is a bar called The Green Sea. It's mostly old men playing cribbage, and on its wall is a portrait of Ben Ali.

At the back round the biggest table is a family you know, playing cards with an Italian deck.

Among them, with his back to you, is your old friend. The eldest of the children. You see him before he sees you.

(link: "Listen")[(set: $alba to $alba + (a: $alba2))
He speaks. The family roars on around, as his old sister winds a trick, him but you hear only this:

<div class="revelation-box">
<em>'$alba2'</em>
</div>

