:: O'Flatterly introduction [venue-cecilcourt] {"position":"300,1700","size":"100,100"}
<span class="shop-bell-marker" style="display:none"></span>(display: "Cecil Rule SVG")
Inis O'Flatterly clocks you, first with his eyes still downcast, then eventually as he looks up. 'You're a novelist and that wasn't a question,' he steams; with the gentle steaming of the kettle, not that of the railway.

(if: $hasMissingPage is true)[<script>setTimeout(function(){if(!window._heardOflatterlyBellPhases)window._heardOflatterlyBellPhases={};if(!window._heardOflatterlyBellPhases['has-page']){window._heardOflatterlyBellPhases['has-page']=true;if(window.dssAudio&&window.dssAudio.doorShopBell)window.dssAudio.doorShopBell();}},100);</script>You hand him the page.

[[Show him the page|Return the page]]]\
(else:)[[[Speak to him|O'Flatterly's quest]]]

:: O'Flatterly's quest [venue-cecilcourt] {"position":"300,1850","size":"100,100"}
'Dear boy,' he burrs, 'I don't know who you are, and don't care who you are, and I don't know that I don't like what you've written; but do me a kindness, kid, and let's just assume I won't need it. Besides, there is something that you must do for me, that we must do together.'

O'Flatterly coughs, disturbing the dust on the cover before him, agitating its thousand motes into flight, which hang over his desk like the clouds over Willesden Junction.

He slaps the manuscript like an arse and says: 'Page 93 is missing. Find it for me!'

(set: $knowsAboutPage to true)

