(else:)[(if: $knowsRonnies is true and $knowsCopperSecret is true and $tookLily4 is false)[<span class="dss-flower-only-marker"></span>](if: _firstColony)[The room is greener than you remember it being but less salad than submarine.

It has crepuscular gravity, of the kind a public house could never muster.

(if: $metRed is true)[As you walk in, Red is leaving; you hold each other's eyes, like clutching pearls, and then he's gone.]](else:)[The room is as you left it. A little too much like you left it.]

(if: $tookLily4 is false)[|lily4>[(display: "Lily SVG")]\
(click-replace: ?lily4)[(set: $lilyCount to $lilyCount + 1)(set: $tookLily4 to true)(display: "Lily SVG")<span class="lily-glimpse lily-fade">Someone in this crowd wears her perfume. You've looked and looked again, she is not here. You know though, that the scent perfume makes is not generic, it is particular to the flesh and blood of she who wears it, born of their live admixture.</span>(if: $lilyHintShown is false)[(set: $lilyHintShown to true)<div class="lily-glimpse-hint">(Gather flowers. There are five to find.)</div>](if: $lilyCount is 5)[(set: $confidence to ($statGain: $confidence, 25))(set: $sobriety to ($statGain: $sobriety, 15))<div class="pent-reveal-note"><div class="pent-reveal-title">⛤ THE PENTACLE ⛤</div><div class="pent-reveal-body">Five flowers, five points; the city draws its star around you.</div><span class="inventory-note">&#9734; MORALE +25 | SOBRIETY +15</span></div><script>setTimeout(function(){if(window.dssRevealPentangleOnMap)window.dssRevealPentangleOnMap();},900);</script>]]](else:)[<div class="lily-taken">(display: "Lily SVG")</div>]

At a table is an agent. There is an impulse among those who work in the book trade, at the business-end of things, to elevate some from their ranks to celebrity. This would not be remarkable (it is done, after all, in most lines of work) were it not for the fact that they deal, in their daily employment, when the job is well done, with remarkable things, deserving of fame. The talented agent, that magus of retail and the markets, is sometimes encouraged, therefore, into a kind of absurd grandeur, which, in the way that prophecies can, will sometimes fulfil itself and serve, valet-like, as its own justification. Such was the agent who sat at the table.

