(else-if: _fc <= 1)[As you walk in the bar drops down to silence, as if its speech were interrupted by a quick gasp for breath, the way a doe sometimes mistakes the wind in the grass for a wolf, stiffens, then goes about its day.

At one end of the bar are the artists; you know them, they are famous.

Stuffed into a barstool which his arsecheeks overhang, like clouds waiting to rain, is a stout man with his back to you. His leather jacket, somehow both parched and sweating, falls short at the neck, flashing a collar of labial pink.

Opposite him is the only man who clocks you, who is thin like verdaccio and hardly there at all.]
(else-if: _fc is 2)[A man cannot step into the same pub twice, because it is not the same pub, and he is not same man.]
(else:)[There is always a third.]

(if: _fc >= 2 and not (($haunts contains $haunt1) and ($haunts contains $haunt2)))[[[Get a drink at the bar|Which drink at the French?]]
