="url(#tnaB2)"/><circle cx="530" cy="1020" r="8" fill="url(#tnaB1)"/><circle cx="18" cy="1120" r="13" fill="url(#tnaB2)"/><circle cx="545" cy="1180" r="10" fill="url(#tnaB1)"/><circle cx="28" cy="1300" r="11" fill="url(#tnaB2)"/><ellipse cx="542" cy="880" rx="4" ry="15" transform="rotate(-8,542,880)" fill="rgba(68,32,7,0.38)"/><ellipse cx="20" cy="1060" rx="3" ry="12" transform="rotate(6,20,1060)" fill="rgba(68,32,7,0.35)"/><circle cx="58" cy="768" r="3" fill="rgba(132,80,28,0.21)"/><circle cx="518" cy="800" r="2.5" fill="rgba(124,74,22,0.19)"/><circle cx="44" cy="842" r="2" fill="rgba(138,84,30,0.18)"/><circle cx="534" cy="912" r="3.5" fill="rgba(128,76,24,0.22)"/><circle cx="26" cy="888" r="2" fill="rgba(142,88,32,0.17)"/><circle cx="548" cy="968" r="2" fill="rgba(122,70,20,0.20)"/><circle cx="66" cy="1000" r="3" fill="rgba(136,82,28,0.19)"/><circle cx="16" cy="1042" r="2.5" fill="rgba(130,78,26,0.18)"/><circle cx="524" cy="1080" r="4" fill="rgba(138,82,30,0.21)"/><circle cx="42" cy="1148" r="2" fill="rgba(124,74,22,0.17)"/><circle cx="538" cy="1220" r="3" fill="rgba(132,80,28,0.20)"/><circle cx="30" cy="1268" r="2.5" fill="rgba(140,86,30,0.19)"/><circle cx="520" cy="1340" r="3.5" fill="rgba(126,76,24,0.21)"/><circle cx="54" cy="1380" r="2" fill="rgba(134,82,28,0.17)"/><line x1="0" y1="900" x2="1000" y2="900" stroke="rgba(155,125,70,0.09)" stroke-width="1.5"/><line x1="0" y1="898" x2="1000" y2="898" stroke="rgba(75,50,20,0.05)" stroke-width="0.8"/><circle cx="22" cy="1450" r="11" fill="url(#tnaB1)"/><circle cx="540" cy="1520" r="9" fill="url(#tnaB2)"/><circle cx="35" cy="1620" r="10" fill="url(#tnaB2)"/><circle cx="530" cy="1700" r="12" fill="url(#tnaB1)"/><circle cx="18" cy="1800" r="11" fill="url(#tnaB2)"/><circle cx="545" cy="1880" r="9" fill="url(#tnaB1)"/><circle cx="28" cy="1980" r="12" fill="url(#tnaB2)"/><circle cx="538" cy="2060" r="10" fill="url(#tnaB1)"/><circle cx="48" cy="1480" r="3" fill="rgba(132,80,28,0.20)"/><circle cx="520" cy="1540" r="2.5" fill="rgba(124,74,22,0.19)"/><circle cx="62" cy="1600" r="2" fill="rgba(138,84,30,0.18)"/><circle cx="534" cy="1660" r="3.5" fill="rgba(128,76,24,0.22)"/><circle cx="16" cy="1740" r="2.5" fill="rgba(142,88,32,0.17)"/><circle cx="548" cy="1820" r="2" fill="rgba(122,70,20,0.20)"/><circle cx="42" cy="1900" r="3" fill="rgba(136,82,28,0.19)"/><circle cx="524" cy="1960" r="2.5" fill="rgba(130,78,26,0.18)"/><circle cx="30" cy="2040" r="3" fill="rgba(138,82,30,0.21)"/><circle cx="520" cy="2120" r="2.5" fill="rgba(132,80,28,0.19)"/><ellipse cx="20" cy="1750" rx="3" ry="12" transform="rotate(6,20,1750)" fill="rgba(68,32,7,0.32)"/><ellipse cx="542" cy="1580" rx="4" ry="14" transform="rotate(-8,542,1580)" fill="rgba(68,32,7,0.35)"/><line x1="0" y1="1500" x2="1000" y2="1500" stroke="rgba(155,125,70,0.07)" stroke-width="1"/></svg>
Autumn, 1973.

Soho, London.

You've written a book and you've a baby at home; tonight, somehow, you'll make them both make sense.

The book took much longer to make than the little girl, and after an immediate, impromptu effort, you can't take much credit for her, either.

She is born now and her mother, Aoife, sits at home, with the babe in her arms.

Home's cold, at home there is not enough food. If she's told you once, she's told you again that there's not enough money coming in. You're a good man so you've taken a job in a warehouse by the flat. But you'll not make enough, not all year.

And so tonight you've gone back to Soho, with your book in your bag and a sense of the place as it was, ten years ago, when //no wife, no house or land still seemed quite natural.//

You'll try, you suppose, the haunts you used to haunt and the people you knew. That'll work: it's a good book and God's a good man.

[[Step into the night|Dean Street]]
</div>

:: Night Ahead Part Two [night-ahead] {"position":"700,350","size":"100,100"}
