(set: $bookTitle to "")\
<div class="nb-input">(input-box: bind $bookTitle, 1)</div>
<div class="nb-subtitle">: A Cover Story</div>
<div class="nb-link-row">(link: "Back to Dean Street.")[(if: $bookTitle is "")[(set: $bookTitle to "Untitled Manuscript")](set: $bookTitle to $bookTitle + ": A Cover Story")(go-to: "Dean Street")]</div>
</div>

<script>
requestAnimationFrame(function() {
  var root = document.querySelector('.book-naming');
  if (!root) return;
  root.classList.add('is-empty');
  var ta = root.querySelector('textarea');
  function syncEmptyState() {
    if (!ta) return;
    var v = (ta.value || '').trim();
    if (v.length > 0) { root.classList.remove('is-empty'); root.classList.add('has-input'); }
    else { root.classList.add('is-empty'); root.classList.remove('has-input'); }
  }
  if (ta) {
    // Harlowe's input-box defaults to rows=2; force single-line.
    ta.rows = 1;
    function fitTitleFont() {
      var len = (ta.value || '').length;
      var size = '1.85em';
      if (len > 28) size = '0.85em';
      else if (len > 22) size = '1.05em';
      else if (len > 16) size = '1.3em';
      else if (len > 12) size = '1.55em';
      ta.style.setProperty('font-size', size, 'important');
    }
    fitTitleFont();
    ta.addEventListener('keydown', function(e) {
      if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.keyCode === 13) e.preventDefault();
      var k = e.key;
      var isCharOrDelete = (k && k.length === 1) || k === 'Backspace' || k === 'Delete';
      if (isCharOrDelete && window.dssAudio && window.dssAudio.typewriterTick) {
        try { window.dssAudio.typewriterTick(0.16); } catch(err) {}
      }
    });
    ta.addEventListener('input', function(){ syncEmptyState(); fitTitleFont(); });
    setTimeout(function() { try { ta.focus({preventScroll: true}); } catch(e) {} }, 200);
    syncEmptyState();
  }
  root.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
    if (e.target.closest('tw-link')) {
      if (ta) ta.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', {bubbles:true}));
    }
  }, true);
});
</script>

:: The Spanish Artist [venue-french] {"position":"500,800","size":"100,100"}
(display: "French Rule SVG h60")
Benito de los Juncales del Oeste has a bottle of chablis, one-third-drunk, in his hand. He ushers you to an empty table, the one where the artists sat before they were too many.

He has the look of a man who is happy to watch the light change.

He takes an empty glass and pours for you.

'You're selling something,' he says. 'It is making you unhappy. You cannot force someone to see what you have made.'

[[Listen|Benito's Hour]]

:: Benito's Hour [venue-french] {"position":"500,850","size":"100,100"}
(display: "French Rule SVG h60")

'In El Rocío, where I am from, there is each Whitsun a pilgrimage. A million pilgrims, on foot and on horses, go for three days through the marshes. They sing; they pray. When they reach the Virgin, they kneel. Next morning they go home again, to work and family. You might say nothing changes, but it does, me amigo, it does.

'In 1962 I painted a small thing – a girl asleep at a window. I was poor. I carried it from door to door in Madrid, to flog it. Nobody bought it. After many weeks I slid it under my bed.

'Six years later, a friend came to help me move house. He saw it as we moved the bed from the bedroom. “This is mine,” he said. And it was; it had waited for him.

'Everything you make already exists. You cannot change that. You make it; they might find it. That's enough. It wants only to live.'

[[Let him look|The Painter's Gaze]]

:: The Painter's Gaze [venue-french] {"position":"500,900","size":"100,100"}
(display: "French Rule SVG h60")

(unless: $haunts is an array)[(set: $haunts to (a:))]
(unless: $haunt1 is a string)[(set: $haunt1 to "The Sketch")]
