:: Sketch the Painter [venue-french] {"position":"500,1000","size":"100,100"}
<style>
.napkin-wrap { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; margin: 1em 0; }
.napkin-canvas { background: #f2e7c9; cursor: crosshair; border: 1px solid rgba(200,170,100,0.35); border-radius: 3px; box-shadow: 0 6px 28px rgba(0,0,0,0.55), inset 0 0 40px rgba(180,140,70,0.15); touch-action: none; max-width: 100%; height: auto; }
.napkin-tools { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.7em; margin-top: 1em; align-items: center; }
.napkin-tools-row { display: flex; gap: 0.55em; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.napkin-color { width: 26px; height: 26px; border-radius: 50%; cursor: pointer; border: 2px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.25); transition: transform 0.15s; }
.napkin-color[data-color="#111111"] { border-color: rgba(212,165,116,0.75); }
.napkin-color:hover { transform: scale(1.15); }
.napkin-color.active { border: 2px solid #f2e7c9; box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(212,165,116,0.8); }
.napkin-btn { background: rgba(0,0,0,0.4); color: #d4a574; padding: 0.35em 0.95em; border: 1px solid rgba(200,170,100,0.4); border-radius: 3px; cursor: pointer; font-family: 'Crimson Text', Georgia, serif; font-size: 0.9em; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-left: 0.5em; }
.napkin-btn:hover { background: rgba(0,0,0,0.6); color: #ffd699; border-color: rgba(212,165,116,0.7); }
.napkin-canvas.napkin-framed {
  border: 8px solid #2a1d10;
  border-radius: 2px;
  padding: 10px;
  background: #f2e7c9;
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px #7a5a30, 0 12px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.75), inset 0 0 30px rgba(90,60,20,0.2);
  transition: border 0.4s ease, padding 0.4s ease, box-shadow 0.4s ease, transform 0.4s ease;
  transform: scale(1.02);
}
.napkin-erase {
  background: #f2e7c9 !important;
  color: #111;
  display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  font-weight: bold; font-size: 20px; line-height: 22px;
  font-family: Georgia, serif;
}
.napkin-size {
  width: 26px; height: 26px; cursor: pointer;
  border: 2px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: rgba(0,0,0,0.35);
  display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  transition: transform 0.15s;
}
.napkin-size:hover { transform: scale(1.15); }
.napkin-size.active {
  border: 2px solid #f2e7c9;
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(212,165,116,0.8);
}
.napkin-size-thin::after { content: ''; width: 4px; height: 4px; background: #d4a574; border-radius: 50%; }
.napkin-size-thick::after { content: ''; width: 10px; height: 10px; background: #d4a574; border-radius: 50%; }
.napkin-btn[disabled] {
  opacity: 0.35;
  cursor: not-allowed;
  pointer-events: none;
}
</style>
<div class="napkin-wrap">
<canvas class="napkin-canvas" id="napkin-canvas" width="400" height="480"></canvas>
<div class="napkin-tools">
<div class="napkin-tools-row">
<div class="napkin-color active" data-color="#111111" style="background:#111111" title="Black"></div>
<div class="napkin-color" data-color="#1e4fd6" style="background:#1e4fd6" title="Blue"></div>
<div class="napkin-color" data-color="#d81f1f" style="background:#d81f1f" title="Red"></div>
<div class="napkin-color" data-color="#f5c518" style="background:#f5c518" title="Yellow"></div>
<div class="napkin-color" data-color="#2aa14a" style="background:#2aa14a" title="Green"></div>
<div class="napkin-color napkin-erase" data-color="#f2e7c9" title="Eraser">×</div>
</div>
<div class="napkin-tools-row">
<div class="napkin-size napkin-size-thin active" data-size="thin" title="Thin line"></div>
<div class="napkin-size napkin-size-thick" data-size="thick" title="Thick line"></div>
<button class="napkin-btn" id="napkin-undo" disabled>Undo</button>
<button class="napkin-btn" id="napkin-clear">Clear</button>
<button class="napkin-btn" id="napkin-done" disabled>Done</button>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<span id="sketch-nav" style="display:none">(link: "nav")[(go-to: "Give him the painting")]</span>

<script>
(function(){
  var canvas = document.getElementById('napkin-canvas');
  if (!canvas) return;
  var ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
  var W = canvas.width, H = canvas.height;

  function drawBackground() {
    ctx.fillStyle = '#f2e7c9';
    ctx.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);
    // Paper grain
    for (var i = 0; i < 2200; i++) {
      var x = Math.random() * W, y = Math.random() * H;
      ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(170,140,80,' + (Math.random() * 0.05) + ')';
      ctx.fillRect(x, y, 1, 1);
    }
    // Faint fold line
    ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(160,130,70,0.08)';
    ctx.lineWidth = 1;
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(0, H/2 + 20); ctx.lineTo(W, H/2 + 20);
    ctx.stroke();
    // Ghost outline — a seated painter with wine glass
    ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(120,100,70,0.32)';
    ctx.lineWidth = 1.2;
    ctx.lineCap = 'round';
    ctx.lineJoin = 'round';
    // Head (oval)
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.ellipse(200, 160, 72, 92, 0, 0, Math.PI * 2);
    ctx.stroke();
    // Hair sweep
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(132, 120);
    ctx.quadraticCurveTo(200, 70, 272, 125);
    ctx.stroke();
    // Eyes
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.arc(174, 155, 6, 0, Math.PI * 2);
    ctx.moveTo(232, 155);
    ctx.arc(226, 155, 6, 0, Math.PI * 2);
    ctx.stroke();
    // Brows
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(160, 140); ctx.lineTo(188, 138);
    ctx.moveTo(212, 138); ctx.lineTo(240, 140);
    ctx.stroke();
    // Nose
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(200, 168);
    ctx.lineTo(192, 205);
    ctx.lineTo(208, 208);
    ctx.stroke();
    // Mouth (faint smile)
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(178, 228);
    ctx.quadraticCurveTo(200, 240, 222, 228);
    ctx.stroke();
    // Jaw / chin shade
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(150, 230);
    ctx.quadraticCurveTo(200, 260, 250, 230);
    ctx.stroke();
    // Collar / shoulders
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(125, 280);
    ctx.quadraticCurveTo(200, 258, 275, 280);
    ctx.stroke();
    // Coat lines
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(125, 280); ctx.lineTo(95, 430);
    ctx.moveTo(275, 280); ctx.lineTo(305, 430);
    ctx.moveTo(200, 265); ctx.lineTo(200, 430);
    ctx.stroke();
    // Lapel
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(175, 285); ctx.lineTo(200, 310); ctx.lineTo(200, 265);
    ctx.moveTo(225, 285); ctx.lineTo(200, 310);
    ctx.stroke();
    // Wine glass in hand
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(310, 350); // bowl top-left
    ctx.lineTo(302, 392); // bowl down
    ctx.lineTo(338, 392);
    ctx.lineTo(330, 350);
    ctx.moveTo(298, 350); ctx.lineTo(342, 350); // rim
    ctx.moveTo(320, 392); ctx.lineTo(320, 420); // stem
    ctx.moveTo(305, 420); ctx.lineTo(335, 420); // foot
    ctx.stroke();
    // Wine level line
    ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(120,60,50,0.22)';
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(302, 370); ctx.lineTo(334, 370);
    ctx.stroke();
  }
  drawBackground();

  var drawing = false;
  var color = '#111111';
  var brushSize = 3.2;
  var lastX = 0, lastY = 0;
  var strokes = []; // recorded user strokes: [{color, width, points:[{x,y}, ...]}, ...]
  var currentStroke = null;

  function updateButtonStates() {
    var doneBtn = document.getElementById('napkin-done');
    var undoBtn = document.getElementById('napkin-undo');
    if (strokes.length > 0) {
      doneBtn.removeAttribute('disabled');
      undoBtn.removeAttribute('disabled');
    } else {
      doneBtn.setAttribute('disabled', '');
      undoBtn.setAttribute('disabled', '');
    }
  }

  function getPos(e) {
    var rect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();
    var sx = canvas.width / rect.width;
    var sy = canvas.height / rect.height;
    var cx, cy;
    if (e.touches && e.touches[0]) {
      cx = e.touches[0].clientX; cy = e.touches[0].clientY;
    } else {
      cx = e.clientX; cy = e.clientY;
    }
    return { x: (cx - rect.left) * sx, y: (cy - rect.top) * sy };
  }

  function startDraw(e) {
    e.preventDefault();
    drawing = true;
    var p = getPos(e);
    lastX = p.x; lastY = p.y;
    currentStroke = { color: color, width: brushSize, points: [{x: p.x, y: p.y}] };
    strokes.push(currentStroke);
    // Small dot on first click for single taps — sized to current brush
    ctx.fillStyle = color;
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.arc(lastX, lastY, Math.max(brushSize / 2, 1), 0, Math.PI * 2);
    ctx.fill();
    updateButtonStates();
  }
  function draw(e) {
    if (!drawing) return;
    e.preventDefault();
    var p = getPos(e);
    ctx.strokeStyle = color;
    ctx.lineWidth = brushSize;
    ctx.lineCap = 'round';
    ctx.lineJoin = 'round';
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(lastX, lastY);
    ctx.lineTo(p.x, p.y);
    ctx.stroke();
    lastX = p.x; lastY = p.y;
    if (currentStroke) currentStroke.points.push({x: p.x, y: p.y});
  }
  function stopDraw() { drawing = false; currentStroke = null; }

  function drawCleanNapkin() {
    ctx.fillStyle = '#f2e7c9';
    ctx.fillRect(0, 0, W, H);
    for (var i = 0; i < 2200; i++) {
      var x = Math.random() * W, y = Math.random() * H;
      ctx.fillStyle = 'rgba(170,140,80,' + (Math.random() * 0.05) + ')';
      ctx.fillRect(x, y, 1, 1);
    }
    ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(160,130,70,0.08)';
    ctx.lineWidth = 1;
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(0, H/2 + 20); ctx.lineTo(W, H/2 + 20);
    ctx.stroke();
  }

  function replayStrokes() {
    strokes.forEach(function(s){
      if (!s.points || s.points.length === 0) return;
      var w = s.width || 3.2;
      ctx.strokeStyle = s.color;
      ctx.fillStyle = s.color;
      ctx.lineWidth = w;
      ctx.lineCap = 'round';
      ctx.lineJoin = 'round';
      if (s.points.length === 1) {
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(s.points[0].x, s.points[0].y, Math.max(w / 2, 1), 0, Math.PI * 2);
        ctx.fill();
        return;
      }
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(s.points[0].x, s.points[0].y);
      for (var i = 1; i < s.points.length; i++) {
        ctx.lineTo(s.points[i].x, s.points[i].y);
      }
      ctx.stroke();
    });
  }

  function clearStrokes() { strokes = []; }

  canvas.addEventListener('mousedown', startDraw);
  canvas.addEventListener('mousemove', draw);
  canvas.addEventListener('mouseup', stopDraw);
  canvas.addEventListener('mouseleave', stopDraw);
  canvas.addEventListener('touchstart', startDraw, {passive: false});
  canvas.addEventListener('touchmove', draw, {passive: false});
  canvas.addEventListener('touchend', stopDraw);

  var colorBtns = document.querySelectorAll('.napkin-color');
  colorBtns.forEach(function(btn){
    btn.addEventListener('click', function(){
      colorBtns.forEach(function(b){ b.classList.remove('active'); });
      btn.classList.add('active');
      color = btn.getAttribute('data-color');
    });
  });

  document.getElementById('napkin-clear').addEventListener('click', function(){
    clearStrokes();
    drawBackground();
    updateButtonStates();
  });

  document.getElementById('napkin-undo').addEventListener('click', function(){
    if (strokes.length === 0) return;
    strokes.pop();
    drawBackground();
    replayStrokes();
    updateButtonStates();
  });

  var sizeBtns = document.querySelectorAll('.napkin-size');
  sizeBtns.forEach(function(btn){
    btn.addEventListener('click', function(){
      sizeBtns.forEach(function(b){ b.classList.remove('active'); });
      btn.classList.add('active');
      brushSize = (btn.getAttribute('data-size') === 'thick') ? 7 : 3.2;
    });
  });

  document.getElementById('napkin-done').addEventListener('click', function(){
    // Reveal: redraw clean napkin without ghost, replay strokes, frame it,
    // pause for the player to admire it, fade the whole napkin out, then
    // navigate. The fade keeps the transition from feeling abrupt.
    var tools = document.querySelector('.napkin-tools');
    if (tools) tools.style.display = 'none';
    drawCleanNapkin();
    replayStrokes();
    canvas.classList.add('napkin-framed');
    canvas.style.cursor = 'default';
    if (window.dssAudio && window.dssAudio.cameraShutter) {
      try { window.dssAudio.cameraShutter(); } catch(e) {}
    }
    // Save the finished drawing so the notebook can render it as an Effect.
    try { localStorage.setItem('dss_napkin', canvas.toDataURL('image/png')); } catch(e) {}
    var fadeTarget = canvas.closest('.napkin-wrap') || canvas.parentElement || canvas;
    setTimeout(function(){
      if (fadeTarget) {
        fadeTarget.style.transition = 'opacity 0.85s ease';
        fadeTarget.style.opacity = '0';
      }
      setTimeout(function(){
        var navEl = document.getElementById('sketch-nav');
        if (navEl) {
          var twLink = navEl.querySelector('tw-link');
          if (twLink) twLink.click();
        }
      }, 900);
    }, 1500);
  });
})();
</script>

:: Give him the painting [venue-french] {"position":"500,1100","size":"100,100"}
(set: $hasDrawing to true)\
You slide the napkin across the table.

He takes it, smiles and gives it back to you.

<div class="item-box">
<div class="item-header">◈ OBJECT ACQUIRED</div>
<div class="item-name">The Napkin Portrait</div>
<div class="item-note">Stored in your notebook. Go there to work on it more.</div>
</div>

[[Step out.|After the painter]]

:: After the painter [outdoor] {"position":"500,1200","size":"100,100"}
(set: $pendingLilyBreath to false)\
(set: $resumingFromCall to false)\
<div class="typewriter-page">
The way you drew the painter is the way the world looks when you step out of the French. Things are faithful to your wild cartoon, until you blink. Then the place scrolls like a fruit machine and pays out Soho, all its stares and faces, its irresistible odds.

[[On.|Dean Street]]
</div>

:: The Stranger at the French [venue-french] {"position":"300,700","size":"100,100"}
(display: "French Rule SVG h60")

As you approach, someone else catches your eye.

He is skeletal, clad in leathers that serve for his skin. His suedehead veils the clean dome of a skull which, were its architecture less Roman, might seem vulnerable, but is, in its neoclassical form, more embolos than eggshell.

You know him as an old friend, from whom you are estranged over some personal business. He eyes you, raising his empty glass, then tilts his head, like a curious velociraptor, towards the bar. He is offering you a drink.

[[Accept his offer|His round]]

(display: "French Rule SVG h24")</svg>

:: The coast of Carthage [carthage-cicadas carthage-shore] {"position":"100,1550","size":"100,100"}
<script>if(window.dssAudio&&window.dssAudio.ambientCut)window.dssAudio.ambientCut();</script>\
<div id="carthage-approach"></div>[[·|Carthage shore]]

:: Carthage shore [carthage-cicadas carthage-shore] {"position":"100,1650","size":"100,100"}
(set: $visitedCarthage to true)\
You've left London. You are many miles and centuries far off. You've found safe harbour in Carthage, which is not like you remember it at all. These days it is swamped with Romans.

Last time you were here, you recall only Scipio Aemilianus, who was your friend and student and who weeping said:

<div class="verse">
'A day will come when Ilium shall perish,<br>
And Priam and his people shall be slain.'
</div>

(link: "⟡ LORE: Carthago Delenda Est ⟡")[<div class="lore-box">
Just north of Tunis and still given succour by the natural exposition of geographies, though piecemeal these days as if it had passed through a grinder, is Carthage harbour. A levelled motte with all Africa as its bailey, the little islet lies flat as a landed coin: the downward face is Hannibal's; that lodged against the sky is inscribed ROMA.

It is hard to know just when or where you are. Foam lingers at the sea's brown lip unnaturally, endures in rabid pinnacles and domes, such as suggests an admixture of plastics. Strange insects spawn into ammonia clouds and chase you where the great galleys once berthed.

Overlooking the harbour is Flaubert's house, or the house that we pretend was his, also in ruins. Stand by its jasmined gates of rotting iron and ask young Scipio just what he meant. He'll tell you true, this is a falling hour.
</div>]

He wept for Rome. You think about that still, sometimes, in England.

There are two paths:

On the hill a queen burns upon a pyre.

And past the beach, a little bar: The Green Sea.

(unless: $visitedPyre is a boolean)[(set: $visitedPyre to false)]\
(set: _carthageDone to ($alba contains $alba2) and ($hasMissingPage is true or $returnedPage is true))\
