<h2 class="venue-title">Trisha's</h2>
The stairs descend through light incarnadine and lead you onto a ship that seems far from Soho because it sails in the calm at the storm's heart.

You enter some eternal afternoon. Years earlier it was perpetual dusk, which is like dawn; balanced; a cocktail stirred, not shaken. Now is the forever afternoon; both the day before and the day after, a kind of grenadine light and frozen-gin time. Mascara running in the Spanish fashion down eyes that would be closed were they not here.

Sessile on the circumambient benches, a woman is a mathematical attractor; that is, all systems tend to move her way. She sits, the Byzantine broad, magnificent, with an angel on each side.

You know who she is, she is Shana, destroyer of worlds.

(if: $metShana is false)[[[Approach Shana|Approach Shana]]]

(if: $knowsRonnies is true and $completedSetlist is false)[[[Ronnie Scott's is nearby.|Approach Ronnie Scott's]] (if: $haunts contains $haunt7)[<span class="hp hp-done">◆</span>](else:)[(if: $hauntExplained is true)[<span class="hp">◇</span>]]]
[[Back to Dean Street|Dean Street]]
<span class="trishas-strip">· · · · · · · · · ·</span></div>

:: Turn to Copper [venue-cellar] {"position":"1600,850","size":"100,100"}
(set: $awaitingCopperPwd to true)\
<!-- Swinging bulb -->
<div class="cellar-bulb-wrap">
<svg width="48" height="90" viewBox="0 0 48 90"><!-- Wire from ceiling --><line x1="24" y1="0" x2="24" y2="30" stroke="#888878" stroke-width="1.4" opacity="0.75"/><!-- Socket cap --><rect x="17" y="28" width="14" height="10" rx="2.5"fill="rgba(80,78,65,0.9)" stroke="rgba(160,155,120,0.7)" stroke-width="1"/><!-- Socket ring detail --><rect x="19" y="36" width="10" height="3" rx="1"fill="none" stroke="rgba(150,145,110,0.55)" stroke-width="0.8"/><!-- Outer glow halo --><ellipse cx="24" cy="60" rx="20" ry="22"fill="rgba(255,245,160,0.12)"/><!-- Bulb body — pear shape, bright and solid --><path d="M24,38 C16,38 10,45 10,55 C10,67 16,78 24,78 C32,78 38,67 38,55 C38,45 32,38 24,38 Z"fill="rgba(255,252,210,0.95)" stroke="rgba(220,210,160,0.6)" stroke-width="0.8"/><!-- Inner warm core --><ellipse cx="24" cy="57" rx="9" ry="11"fill="rgba(255,240,120,0.55)"/><!-- Filament — W-shape --><path d="M18,60 L20,53 L24,58 L28,53 L30,60"fill="none" stroke="rgba(255,200,40,0.95)" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linejoin="round"/><!-- Neck base ring --><rect x="20" y="75" width="8" height="3" rx="1"fill="rgba(200,195,155,0.65)" stroke="none"/></svg>
</div>
<div class="cellar-scene">
<div class="cellar-light"></div>
'Come in then,' says Copper.

You do as you're told and he closes the door behind you.

'Down them stairs.'

You don't remember it being downstairs.

Salvu Copper is a big man in a small body, or the other way round.

You both barrel into a cellar. It runs, you can be sure, at least beneath the Colony Rooms and probably one house further.

'Salvu Copper' is a name you know and now you're putting a face to it.

Since the Twins went down in '68, his work's been easier. He's run his little fiefdom – pornography, strip clubs, hookers (the sorts of work that old fashioned East End crooks will swear blind they don't touch) – very nicely, though lately he's feeling the heat.

At the far end of the cellar, at a simple wooden table, sits 'Quiet' Frankie Muscat, who seems to you like nothing so much as a planet, the sort of man with moons. Yes, he is big, but his gravity comes, mostly, from his silence and a sense of power unused.

Opposite him (and her presence surprises you) is a poet you know, an American girl who comes from banking money, called Ashton Granger. You agreed long ago to pretend not to notice each other, should you accidentally meet. She twirls her hair and scribbles without looking at the page, and gives Quiet Frankie a kind of angry come-hither look.

'So who are you?' says Copper. 'And what do you imagine you've got to say for yourself?'

(if: $knowsCopperWord)[<div id="copper-pwd-wrap" style="text-align:center;margin-top:1.2em;">
<input type="text" id="copper-pwd-input" placeholder="Say the words…" style="background:#0d0806;color:#d4a574;border:1px solid #8a4a3a;padding:6px 14px;font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:1em;width:220px;outline:none;" />
<button id="copper-pwd-btn" style="background:#1a0a08;color:#d4a574;border:1px solid #8a4a3a;padding:6px 18px;font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:1em;cursor:pointer;margin-left:6px;">Say it</button>
<p style="font-size:0.78em;color:#7a6a5a;margin-top:0.6em;letter-spacing:0.05em;">If you can't remember the password, check your notebook.</p>
</div>
<span id="go-copper-yes" style="display:none">[[·|Copper Word Accepted]]</span>
<span id="go-copper-no" style="display:none">[[·|Copper confronts]]</span>
]
(else:)[[[Say nothing|Copper confronts]]]
</div>

:: Watch the decider [venue-lackland-back] {"position":"1200,1300","size":"100,100"}
Jack Curtis wins it. Smash to the corner.

'Fancy the game?' says Jack Curtis.

'House rules,' says Percy Ritson, 'winner plays the stranger.' He turns to you. 'Unless the stranger fancies an easier task, in which case I'll take you off Jack's hands.'

(link: "Challenge Jack Curtis")[(set: $ppScore to 0)(set: $oppScore to 0)(set: $opponent to "Jack Curtis")(go-to: "PP Pong")]
(link: "Challenge Percy Ritson")[(set: $ppScore to 0)(set: $oppScore to 0)(set: $opponent to "Percy Ritson")(go-to: "PP Pong")]

